# Notebook Editing Conventions

When editing any `notebook.md` file in this repository:

## Structure Preservation

- Never delete section headers (##, ###), blockquotes (>), or italicized guidance text.
- Never reorder the SIMILAR phase sections — they must remain in S-I-M-I-L-A-R order.
- Add content below guidance prompts, not in place of them.
- HTML comments (`<!-- AGENT: ... -->`) are facilitator notes — read them for guidance but never delete them.

## Table Editing

- Add new rows to tables — never overwrite or delete the header row.
- When a table has example placeholder rows (empty cells), replace them with content, then add more rows as needed.

## Metadata

- Update `Last Updated` in the Metadata table whenever you edit the notebook.
- When creating a sub-notebook, set its `Parent Notebook` field to a relative link back to the parent.
- Keep `Phase status` lines accurate — update them as work progresses through each phase.

## Decision Log

- Record every significant design choice in the Decision Log section.
- Include: date, what was decided, why (rationale), what else was considered, and which SIMILAR phase it relates to.

## Content Style

- Requirements use "shall/must" (mandatory) or "should" (tradeoff) — enforce this vocabulary.
- Never introduce the word "optimal", "maximize", "minimize", or "simultaneous" into requirements.
- State requirements as WHAT the system must do, not HOW to implement it.
